"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"### Contents\\n\\n* Direct fiat-to-L2 onboarding\\n* L2 bridges\\n* L2 compatible wallets\\n* L2s and dApps\\n* More L2 info\\n\\n### Direct fiat-to-L2 onboarding\\n\\n[layerswap.io](http://layerswap.io) You can transfer funds from \\\\[Binance, Coinbase, Huobi, FTX, Kucoin\\\\] to \\\\[Arbitrum, Optimism, Boba\\\\]\\n\\n[binance.com](https://binance.com) has integrated with Arbitrum\\n\\n[crypto.com](http://crypto.com) has integrated with Arbitrum\\n\\n[go.ramp.network/zkSync](https://go.ramp.network/zkSync) direct fiat to zkSync! (not for US)\\n\\n### L2 bridges\\n\\n[hop.exchange](https://hop.exchange) \\\\[mainnet, Optimism, Arbitrum\\\\] → \\\\[mainnet, Optimism, Arbitrum\\\\]. Hop seems to be the most popular bridge so far.\\n\\n[xpollinate.io](https://xpollinate.io/) \\\\[mainnet, Optimism, Arbitrum\\\\] → \\\\[mainnet, Optimism, Arbitrum\\\\]\\n\\n[portr.xyz](http://Portr.xyz) mainnet -> Optimism\\n\\n[cbridge.celer.network/#/transfer](https://cbridge.celer.network/#/transfer) \\\\[mainnet, Optimism, Arbitrum, Boba\\\\] → \\\\[mainnet, Optimism, Arbitrum, Boba\\\\]\\n\\n[synapseprotocol.com](https://synapseprotocol.com/) \\\\[mainnet, Optimism, Arbitrum, Boba\\\\] → \\\\[mainnet, Optimism, Arbitrum, Boba\\\\]\\n\\n[anyswap.exchange](https://anyswap.exchange) \\\\[mainnet, Arbitrum, Boba\\\\] → \\\\[mainnet, Arbitrum, Boba\\\\]\\n\\n[across.to](https://across.to) \\\\[Arbitrum, Optimism\\\\] -> mainnet\\n\\n[li.finance](https://li.finance) goes cross-chain and can swap for other tokens, so you can put in ETH on mainnet and get DAI on Optimism; it’ll find the cheapest route for you.\\n\\n### L2 compatible wallets\\n\\nPlease see [github.com/ethereum/ethereum-org-website/issues/4520#issuecomment-976841120](https://github.com/ethereum/ethereum-org-website/issues/4520#issuecomment-976841120)\\n\\n### L2s and dApps\\n\\nArbitrum: [portal.arbitrum.one](https://portal.arbitrum.one)\\n\\nOptimism: [optimism.io/apps/all](https://optimism.io/apps/all)\\n\\nzkSync: [zksync.community/t/links-to-applications-making-use-of-zksync/15](https://www.zksync.community/t/links-to-applications-making-use-of-zksync/15)\\n\\nYou can also donate to projects on Gitcoin via zkSync!\\n\\nBoba: [boba.network/ecosystem/](https://boba.network/ecosystem/) (scroll down)\\n\\nAnother way to see available dApps: go to [DeFi Llama](https://defillama.com/) and filter by the L2 you’re interested in. This may not include the newest dApps, but you can see the TVL in the most popular ones.\\n\\nFor DAOs, the most popular DAO tool [Gnosis Safe](https://gnosis-safe.io/) supports Arbitrum.\\n\\n### More L2 info\\n\\nA rollup-centric ethereum roadmap, by Vitalik Buterin [ethereum-magicians.org/t/a-rollup-centric-ethereum-roadmap/4698](https://ethereum-magicians.org/t/a-rollup-centric-ethereum-roadmap/4698)\\n\\nWritings of [@epolynya](https://twitter.com/epolynya), who pushed the idea of modular blockchains into the mainstream: [polynya.medium.com](https://polynya.medium.com)\\n\\nComparisons between L2s (TVL, types of risks): [l2beat.com](https://l2beat.com)\\n\\nL2 fees: [l2fees.info](https://l2fees.info)\\n\\nIn-depth writeup on different L2s and L2 tools: [mirror.xyz/dcbuilder.eth/QX_ELJBQBm1Iq45ktPsz8pWLZN1C52DmEtH09boZuo0](https://mirror.xyz/dcbuilder.eth/QX_ELJBQBm1Iq45ktPsz8pWLZN1C52DmEtH09boZuo0)\\n\\n\\n***\\n\\nI only included L2s that currently support smart contracts - will update as more smart contract L2s go live.\\n\\nPlease reach out to [@ethmaxitard](https://twitter.com/ethmaxitard) if you have any suggestions. (I threw this together at the [@CodelessCon](https://twitter.com/CodelessCon) codeless web3 hackathon!)\",\"timestamp\":1639268221,\"title\":\"Ethereum L2 Cheatsheet\"},\"digest\":\"v1ZUmHUQPlGky8vRVIZG5FDdOp5un9XJeQ8K-K5CWu8\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xff346ea3639181ecd8A499b066f6452a4bC9B1E3\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"